ce:section.ce:para:
With satisfactory sensitivity and selectivity, the applicability of the new dual-model immunoassay was evaluated in real samples. According to the linear ranges, various concentrations of AFB1 spiked corn samples (0, 0.8, 1.2, 1.6 ng/mL) were applied to achieve the recovery studies. The recoveries of fluorescence assay were from 98.75 % to 104.25 %, and absorbance assay were from 93.63 % to 104.63 %. In addition, the coefficient of variation was less than 5 % (
                        Table 1

                        ). These results met the standard of American Association of Analytical Chemists (AOAC). Meanwhile, the results of the two models were consistent, indicating that the two models can be mutually verified (
                        Table 1
                        ). Above results indicated the dual-model immunoassay had high accuracy for AFB1 detection in real samples.
